Analyzing the monthly sales data, several key insights emerge that can guide business strategies for Kuzebikes:

1Ô∏è‚É£ Peak Sales Performance (High Revenue & Orders)
- April 2018: 125 orders, generating $909,179.47 with an average order value of $2,361.51.
- January 2018: 52 orders, $426,301.72 revenue, higher average order value ($2,631.49) than April.

‚úÖ Insight: April 2018 saw the highest demand, suggesting it might be a peak season for bicycle purchases.
‚úÖ Action: Consider inventory expansion and targeted promotions for similar months.

2Ô∏è‚É£ Seasonality & Trends
- Early months (January‚ÄìApril 2018) had strong sales.
- Mid-year (June 2017, March 2018, August 2017) showed steady but lower performance.
- Late-year (November‚ÄìDecember) saw a significant decline, indicating reduced demand.

‚úÖ Insight: The business experiences seasonal fluctuations‚Äîstrong early-year sales and weaker performance at year's end.
‚úÖ Action: Plan marketing campaigns & discounts toward year-end to boost revenue.

3Ô∏è‚É£ Low Sales Months (Potential Concerns)
- June 2018: Only 1 order, generating $209.99.
- October 2018: Only 1 order, $4,219.92 revenue.
- September 2018: 1 order, $9,949.96, highest average order value ($3,316.65).

‚úÖ Insight: Sporadic sales in mid and late 2018 suggest possible market saturation or demand shift.
